# Fluff Date: 2026-03-12 16:14:59
<overview>
<p>Handheld weapons are heavy equipment built on firearm-like mounts scaled for BattleMech use. The concept spent centuries as little more than an idea. Early Terran Hegemony efforts to create portable weapon mounts for designs like the Griffin and Phoenix Hawk produced only jettison-capable weapons, failing due to weight and bulk issues as well as the lack of safeguards to prevent hostile units from seizing them in combat. Federated Commonwealth researchers revived the concept in 3050, producing the first true handheld weapon prototypes by 3055 in the wake of the Clan Invasion. Even so, the technology struggled to gain acceptance and leave the testing stage until the 3080s. Handheld weapon packages have since been developed in a range of sizes and configurations, from simple one-ton tools built for IndustrialMechs to twelve-ton weapon systems designed for frontline BattleMechs equipped with triple strength myomer.</p>
</overview>

<capabilities>
<p>The Rocket Launcher Weapon is a two-ton handheld weapon package designed for the Exo HaulerMech produced by Waytani, Inc. It mounts four Rocket Launcher 10 packs, providing a substantial one-time volley of forty rockets. Rocket launchers are single-use weapons that cannot be reloaded in the field, making this package a disposable but powerful option. The concentrated salvo can threaten even armored vehicles, giving an otherwise unarmed IndustrialMech a meaningful first strike. Once all four packs are expended, the empty weapon assembly is dead weight.</p>
</capabilities>

